HEADWORD: Windle
<hw>Win"dle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Wind</er> to
turn.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A spindle; a kind of reel; a winch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The redwing.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Windless</ent>⟦br⟧
